claims:
1. A method for controlling a mechanical ventilator to provide mid-frequency mandatory ventilation to a patient comprising:
providing mandatory ventilation to a patient according to a ventilation pattern;
monitoring an alveolar ventilation of the patient;
determining one of an optimal frequency, an optimal duty cycle, and an optimal positive end expiratory pressure for the mechanical ventilator according to the alveolar ventilation of the patient; and
updating the ventilation pattern of the mechanical ventilator to include the determined one of the optimal frequency, the optimal duty cycle, and the optimal positive end expiratory pressure.

15. A computer readable medium storing computer executable instructions for controlling a mechanical ventilator to provide mid-frequency mandatory ventilation to a patient, such that, upon execution in a computer processor, the executable instructions are configured to perform a iterative method comprising the steps of:
instructing the mechanical ventilator to provide mandatory ventilation to a patient according to a ventilation pattern;
monitoring the feedback value representing an alveolar ventilation of the patient; and
adjusting a duty cycle of the ventilation pattern according to the feedback value;
wherein the iterative method is continued until a termination event is detected, such that a plurality of adjusted duty cycles and associated feedback values are collected.
